#: Source/Guidelines/en/CC-LanguageCorpora.xml:127
msgid ""
"The <_:gi-1/> element is intended for the encoding of language corpora, "
"though it may also be useful in encoding newspapers, electronic anthologies, "
"and other disparate collections of material. The individual samples in the "
"corpus are encoded as separate <_:gi-2/> elements, and the entire corpus is "
"enclosed in a <_:gi-3/> element. Each sample has the usual structure for a "
"<_:gi-4/> document, comprising a <_:gi-5/> followed by a <_:gi-6/> element. "
"The corpus, too, has a corpus-level <_:gi-7/> element, in which the corpus "
"as a whole, and encoding practices common to multiple samples may be "
"described. The overall structure of a TEI-conformant corpus is thus: <_:"
