msgid ""
"Language corpora often include analytic encodings or annotations, designed "
"to support a variety of different views of language. The present Guidelines "
"do not advocate any particular approach to linguistic annotation (or <_:"
"soCalled-1/>); instead a number of general analytic facilities are provided "
"which support the representation of most forms of annotation in a standard "
"and self-documenting manner. Analytic annotation is of importance in many "
"fields, not only in corpus linguistics, and is therefore discussed in "
"general terms elsewhere in the Guidelines.<_:note-2/> The present section "
"presents informally some particular applications of these general mechanisms "
"to the specific practice of corpus linguistics."
